# VeriLearn — environment configuration
# Copy to `web/.env.local` (git-ignored) for local dev, or set these in your
# host's environment for a deployment. Only the app in web/ reads these.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# REQUIRED IN PRODUCTION
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Secret used to HMAC-sign session cookies and the verify-endpoint envelope.
# MUST be set to a long, random, secret value in production — the app refuses
# to boot in production without it (it will not fall back to the insecure dev
# default). Generate one with:  openssl rand -hex 32
VERILEARN_SESSION_SECRET=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set automatically by the framework — listed for reference only.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NODE_ENV=production   # `next build && next start` sets this; don't set by hand.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DEFERRED — not read by the app yet. These are the production adapters that
# sit behind clean seams today (see docs/architecture/decisions/0001-*.md and
# docs/IMPLEMENTATION.md). Add the real keys here when those adapters land:
#   - DATABASE_URL             (managed Postgres, replacing the in-memory store)
#   - STRIPE_SECRET_KEY        (billing)
#   - LLM_API_KEY              (the real verifier / Skeptic)
#   - SMTP_* / EMAIL_API_KEY   (transactional email)
#   - OIDC_* / SAML_*          (SSO / SCIM / LTI)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
